    54	
    55	<objective>
    56	Add Numpress-linear m/z compression to the chunked spectra_data layout and make it the new default.
    57	A vendored, pure-managed C# MSNumpress port encodes each chunk's sorted m/z into a `mz_numpress_linear_bytes`
    58	list<uint8> column (7th chunk field), `mz_chunk_values` becomes null, `chunk_encoding = MS:1002312`, and the
    59	intensity list stays the plain lossless `large_list<float>`. `--no-numpress` / `--lossless` falls back to the
    60	Phase-2 delta chunks (bitwise-L1); `--point` falls back to the v1 point layout (bitwise-L1).
    61	
    62	LOCKED scope: intensity stays lossless f32. We do NOT implement intensity Numpress-SLOF (the reference does;
    63	that drives its ~63% total reduction). Our numpress output is therefore a VALID m/z-only-numpress variant of
    64	the chunk schema, intentionally NOT byte/schema-identical to small.numpress.mzpeak. Intensity-SLOF is backlog.
    65	
    66	Purpose: smallest m/z encoding (the size win), self-describing transform, bounded L2 m/z fidelity while
    67	intensity remains exact. Output: the MSNumpress codec + numpress chunk emission + CLI default + L2/3-mode
    68	verification.
    69	</objective>
