   148	    - OptimalLinearFixedPoint(double[]) returns the least-squares optimal fixed point (matches pynumpress.optimal_linear_fixed_point exactly on m/z arrays).
   149	    - EncodeLinear(double[], long fp): 8-byte BE-double fixed-point prefix, first two values as 5-byte LE fixed-point ints, residuals as 4-bit half-byte varints (encodeInt). EncodeLinear(double[]) overload computes fp internally.
   150	    - DecodeLinear(byte[]) reconstructs the array; round-trip max|Δ| <= 0.5/fp.
   151	    - Known vector: data=[100.0,100.5,101.0,101.5], fp=21367996 -> hex 417460cbc000000070f95c7fceffff7f88; decode is exact.
   152	    - Edge cases: empty array -> empty bytes (and decode of <=8 bytes -> empty); single value; two values (no residuals); ascending m/z slices of length 1..N.
   153	    - Cross-check vs pynumpress (python3.11): C#-encode bytes == pynumpress.encode_linear bytes for the same fp; pynumpress.decode_linear(C#-bytes) within bound.
   154	    - phantom-leading-value: anchor decode to chunk start/end is the CALLER's concern (Task 2 test); the codec returns the raw MSNumpress decode. Document the artifact in the codec header note (no harness/phase wording).
