   260	
   261	</tasks>
   262	
   263	<threat_model>
   264	## Trust Boundaries
   265	
   266	| Boundary | Description |
   267	|----------|-------------|
   268	| RAW scan data → numpress encoder | Untrusted/variable m/z arrays (empty, single-point, near-equal, non-monotone) cross into the codec |
   269	| vendored ms-numpress source → assembly | Third-party algorithm ported into our managed assembly |
   270	| numpress bytes → archive consumers | Lossy m/z bytes must be self-describing (transform CURIE) for downstream readers |
   271	
   272	## STRIDE Threat Register
   273	
   274	| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
   275	|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
   276	| T-03-01 | Tampering | Numpress encode/decode correctness | mitigate | Known ms-numpress test vector byte-identity + pynumpress cross-check + per-chunk L2 bound assertion (Tasks 1,4) |
   277	| T-03-02 | Tampering | x64 dependency reintroduction | mitigate | Pure-managed AnyCPU port (System only); explicit AnyCPU/MSIL assembly assertion in tests (Task 1) |
   278	| T-03-03 | Information disclosure | Self-describing transform | mitigate | MS:1002312 recorded in array_index footer + cv_list + data_processing lossy note (Task 2) |
   279	| T-03-04 | Denial of service | Pathological m/z slices (empty/single/2/near-equal) | mitigate | Codec edge-case tests; encoder must terminate on all slice lengths (Task 1) |
   280	| T-03-05 | Repudiation | --lossless/--point silently lossy | accept→mitigate | Bitwise-L1 locks keep both modes exact; CLI warning only in numpress mode (Tasks 3,4) |
   281	| T-03-SC | Tampering | npm/pip/cargo installs | n/a | No package-manager installs introduced; ms-numpress is vendored source, not a package; python3.11/pynumpress used only as a test oracle (pre-existing on system) |
   282	</threat_model>
   283	
   284	<verification>
   285	- Build clean native arm64 Release (writer + test projects).
   286	- Full NUnit suite green native arm64 (Phase-1/2 regressions + new MSNumpress + numpress locks).
   287	- mzpeak-validate 0 errors on small.RAW in numpress (default), --lossless, --point.
   288	- L2: decoded numpress m/z within 0.5/fp vs --lossless; intensity bit-exact f32; --lossless/--point bitwise-L1.
   289	- Size: numpress spectra_data.parquet < delta-chunked spectra_data.parquet.
   290	- No x64 marker: writer/test assemblies AnyCPU (MSIL).
   291	</verification>
   292	
   293	<success_criteria>
   294	- NP-01: pure-managed AnyCPU C# MSNumpress-linear encode+decode, no x64 dep, native arm64. ✓ Task 1
   295	- NP-02: m/z in mz_numpress_linear_bytes with chunk_encoding/transform MS:1002312, recorded in array_index AND data_processing. ✓ Task 2
   296	  (Deviation noted vs ROADMAP "MS:1003089": the verified reference dump shows numpress = MS:1002312; MS:1003089 is delta. We use MS:1002312.)
   297	- NP-03: numpress ON by default; --no-numpress/--lossless -> delta chunks; lossy note in data_processing + CLI warning; --point -> v1. ✓ Task 3
   298	- NP-04: decoded m/z within Numpress-linear bound (0.5/fp) vs source; intensity stays lossless f32. ✓ Tasks 2,4
   299	- Must NOT regress: validator 0/0 all three modes; --lossless/--point bitwise-L1; streaming per-chunk encode preserved. ✓ Task 4
   300	- Scope lock honored: intensity is plain f32 (no SLOF); intensity-SLOF deferred to backlog.
   301	</success_criteria>
   302	
   303	<risks>
   304	- **Numpress port correctness / L2 bound (chief):** the residual 4-bit half-byte varint and 5-byte LE fixed-point packing are the easiest places to mis-port. Mitigated by the ms-numpress known vector (byte-identity), pynumpress byte cross-check at a shared fp, and the per-chunk 0.5/fp decode assertion. The phantom-leading-value decode artifact is handled in the codec's anchor-aligned decode helper, not the raw codec.
   305	- **Reintroducing an x64 dependency:** port uses System only; AnyCPU/MSIL assembly assertion guards against an accidental native pull-in.
   306	- **Keeping --lossless/--point bit-exact:** numpress is gated behind a flag and a separate struct/footer; the delta path and point path are untouched, and bitwise-L1 locks fail loudly if either regresses.
   307	- **CURIE discrepancy:** ROADMAP says MS:1003089 for numpress; verified dump says MS:1002312. We follow the verified artifact and document the override.
   308	- **Size win is m/z-only:** without intensity SLOF the reduction is the m/z saving (not the reference's ~63%). The size lock asserts numpress < delta-chunked (the achievable target), not the reference's headline.
   309	</risks>
   310	
   311	<dependencies>
   312	- Phase 2 (02-01): chunk codec, ChunkFacetStream/ISpectraDataFacet seam, ChunkStructField/ChunkedSpectrumArrayIndex footer, --point/--chunk-size, cv_list registration machinery. Extend, do not fork.
   313	- Phase 1: streaming Parquet Handle (OpenAsync/WriteRowGroupAsync/CloseAsync), NestedLevels/ListOf nested-level computer.
   314	- Runtime: native arm64 .NET (AnyCPU 8.0.37) via DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD; arch -arm64 dotnet for test/convert; mzpeak-validate; python3.11 + pynumpress (test oracle only, Ignored if absent).
   315	- ms-numpress canonical algorithm (Apache-2.0) — vendored as source per RESEARCH-port.md.
   316	</dependencies>
   317	
   318	<output>
   319	Create `.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-SUMMARY.md` when done.
   320	</output>

